article.description: — Devin Carter had 24 points, 12 rebounds and four steals in Providence's 71-58 victory against Georgetown on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Carter's 24 points, 12 rebounds lead Providence over Georgetown 71-58
article.linkText: Carter's 24 points, 12 rebounds lead Providence over Georgetown 71-58
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Devin Carter had 24 points, 12 rebounds and four steals in Providence's 71-58 victory against Georgetown on Tuesday night. Carter scored 20 points in the second half. Josh Oduro scored 14 points and added nine rebounds for the Friars (19-11, 10-9 Big East Conference). Rich Barron finished with 11 points. Jayden Epps led the way for the Hoyas (9-21, 2-17) with 16 points and four steals. Dontrez Styles added 13 points and eight rebounds for Georgetown. Drew Fielder finished with 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
